==Further reading==
* Breay, Clare and Meehan, Bernard (eds), &quot;The St Cuthbert Gospel: Studies on the Insular Manuscript of the Gospel of John&quot;, 2015, British Library, , &quot;scholarly pieces on Cuthbert in his historical context; the codicology, text, script and medieval history of the manuscript; the structure and decoration of the binding; the other relics found in Cuthbert&#x27;s coffin; and the post-medieval ownership of the book&quot;.

