== Topological concepts in terms of closure ==

=== Refinements and subspaces ===
A pair of Kuratowski closures formula_204 such that formula_205 for all formula_73 induce topologies formula_207 such that formula_208, and vice versa. In other words, formula_209 dominates formula_210 if and only if the topology induced by the latter is a refinement of the topology induced by the former, or equivalently formula_211. For example, formula_212 clearly dominates formula_213(the latter just being the identity on formula_2). Since the same conclusion can be reached substituting formula_215 with the family formula_216 containing the complements of all its members, if formula_109 is endowed with the partial order formula_218 for all formula_73 and formula_111 is endowed with the refinement order, then we may conclude that formula_152 is an antitonic mapping between posets.

In any induced topology (relative to the subset &quot;A&quot;) the closed sets induce a new closure operator that is just the original closure operator restricted to &quot;A&quot;: formula_222, for all formula_223.

=== Continuous maps, closed maps and homeomorphisms ===
A function formula_224 is continuous at a point formula_225 iff formula_226, and it is continuous everywhere iff formula_227 for all subsets formula_73. The mapping formula_229 is a closed map iff the reverse inclusion holds, and it is a homeomorphism iff it is both continuous and closed, i.e. iff equality holds.

